* Terraform
** Definition
*** ====<size:14>**Terraform** is an open-source Infrastructure as Code **(IaC)** tool developed by HashiCorp, used for provisioning and managing infrastructure in a declarative manner.

** Key Concepts
*** Infrastructure as Code **(IaC)**
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Managing infrastructure through code and automation.
*** Declarative Configuration
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Describing desired infrastructure state without specifying how to achieve it.
*** HCL **(HashiCorp Configuration Language)**
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>The domain-specific language used to write Terraform configurations.
*** Providers
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Plugins that interface with various infrastructure platforms.
*** Resources
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Infrastructure components like servers, databases, and networks.
*** Modules
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Reusable, shareable Terraform configurations.
*** State File
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>A record of the current infrastructure state.
*** Plan and Apply
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>The process of generating and applying infrastructure changes.

** Terraform Workflow
*** Initialize
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Setting up Terraform working directory.
*** Plan
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Generating an execution plan for changes.
*** Apply
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Applying the execution plan to create or modify infrastructure.
*** Destroy
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Destroying infrastructure resources.
*** Import
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Bringing existing resources under Terraform management.

** Terraform Configurations
*** Variables
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Input values for Terraform configurations.
*** Outputs
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Values to be displayed after infrastructure creation.
*** Data Sources
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>External data retrieval for configurations.
*** Provisioners
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Running scripts on resources after creation.
*** Remote Backends
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Storing Terraform state remotely for collaboration.
*** Workspaces
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Isolating and managing multiple environments.

** Terraform Ecosystem
*** Community Providers
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Third-party providers for various services.
*** Terraform Cloud
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>SaaS platform for remote execution and collaboration.
*** Terraform Enterprise
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Self-hosted enterprise version of Terraform.
*** Sentinel
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Policy as Code for enforcing compliance and security.
*** Terraform Modules Registry
****[#yellow] ====<size:14>Repository for sharing and discovering Terraform modules.

